text:
Be cautious of these CROOKS when they go to slide your debit card. They'll tell you the total is one thing. But when you go to look at your bank statement, you will see that you were charged a little extra.

I ordered a meal and the total came out to $24.75, which is also what I was told over the phone when I was placing my order. I went to pick up my meal. Then I got home and thought nothing of it. Now mind you, I have push notifications enabled on my bank app on my phone that shows me what I recently spent my money on. I saw that BaBa's Kitchen charged me $29.70 for that meal. I decided not to go up there and raise hell over the five measily dollars that they overcharged me. I'll just withdraw my services from them entirely and never order from them again. They just lost a customer. Hope it was worth the $5 stupid dollars.
First off the food is delicious, they also do delivery. Lunch specials are great you get a bunch of stuff for 7 bucks and the people work here are super nice and welcoming.

This place would definitely need a little work, the menu inside the restaurant only showed the boba menu and my phone order wasn't ready after 30min.! The staff here is very friendly though...

The food is 6/10 average, I would recommend a bit more spices on the chow fun and the Kung pao chicken wasn't that spicy. Let me tell you, sriracha would kick it up a bit.

We saw that this place had 4 stars on yelp, so decided to order for delivery. Omg, don't waste your money! The egg flower soup is orange and tastes like water. We ordered 1 chicken and 1 beef dish and orange chicken. The textures of the meats were so odd, they don't even seem like meat. Who knows what they have been soaked in! The orange chicken was dry, no sauce what so ever. Worst Chinese food ever!
this is the only Chinese restaurant that doesnt use MSG!!  they deliver to. the food is great.
